# ADR discipline

Major design decisions live in `docs/adr/`. See `docs/adr/README.md` for layout.

## Layout

- **Folder:** `docs/adr/YYYY-MM-DD/` — date of the decision session. No version suffix (`v1`, `v2`) in folder names.
- **Batch README:** what this session decided; links to topic files.
- **Topic file:** one major decision per `topic-slug.md` inside the date folder.

**New session → new date folder.** Single urgent decision can be its own folder with one file.

## Cross-references

Use **Relates to:** / **Supersedes:** with relative links across date folders, e.g. `../2026-06-19/embedding-providers-by-environment.md`.

When reversing a decision: mark old file `superseded`, add new topic file (new date folder if new session), link both ways.

## Write an ADR when

- Choosing or changing providers, schema, auth, deploy topology
- Cost, security, or environment-splitting trade-offs

Skip bug fixes, refactors without decision change, dependency bumps.

## Keep in sync

- **`ARCHITECTURE.md`** — how the system works now
- **`docs/adr/`** — why choices were made
- **`docs/adr/README.md`** — batch index when adding folders
- **`TODO.md`** — deferred work from ADR consequences
